Centimes in lower case with value tables in black. 
Design from a photograph of Haile Selassie I in coronation robes. The stamps were printed by lithography by Nasik Security Printing in India, and the value tablets typographed by McCorquidale & Co., Khartoum, Sudan. The sheets were 72 stamps (9 x 8) with the values printed on one-third sheet (3 x 8) in three runs.
</p>
