During the Italian occupation, Italy issued stamps for __Africa Orientale Italiana__. 
Following Italy's defeat
in 1941, haile Selassie resumed issuing Ethiopian stamps (1942), the first three printed in India. Increasingly
Ethiopian, culture, flora and fauna became the subject of Ethiopian philately.

During the __Derg__ regime, political themes also became popular.

